=== host_discovery_with_nmap ===

ping sweep/ping scan

Find out your current IP address
ip a

10.0.2.15

nmap
built into kali

--- commands ---
sudo nmap -sn (no port scan)
sudo nmap -sn 10.0.0.0/24 | grep “<domain>”
netdiscover - resolves mac addresses to ip addresses
sudo netdiscover -i eth0 -r 10.0.0.0/24



--- activity ---
sudo nmap -sn 10.0.0.0/24
displays hosts that are up and associated to the domain

Gather the ip/host information

sudo netdiscover -i eth0 -r 10.0.0.0/24

also refer to subnets

10.0.1.0/24
10.0.2.0/24

Gather the information here as well
